e> by default generates an executable named <code data-start=3D"289" data-e=
nd=3D"296">a.exe</code> (on Windows) or <code data-start=3D"313" data-end=
=3D"320">a.out</code> (on Linux/Mac).</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"339" data-end=3D"414">
<p data-start=3D"341" data-end=3D"414">With <code data-start=3D"346" data-e=
nd=3D"361">-o &lt;filename&gt;</code>, you specify the name of the generate=
